                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/edsl-350" class="program-course-title">
              EDSL 350 Essentials of English Grammar (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-24218" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Integrated Studies in Ed (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/608">Faculty of Education</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Education in Second Languages              : Analysis of English phrases, clauses and sentences up to discourse level in connected text. Emphasis on distinguishing between grammatical form, meaning, and function. Identification, analysis and correction of common errors made by ESL learners.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        Mekhala Sarkar (Fall)                  </p>

    
