                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/ling-355" class="program-course-title">
              LING 355 Language Acquisition 1 (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29206" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Linguistics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Linguistics              : A critical study of the application of linguistic theory and description to first and second language learning. Topics include: the acquisition of sounds, syntax and word meanings; acquisition strategies; properties of the input; theories of first and second language acquisition.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:              There are no professors associated with this course for the 2014-2015 academic year.          </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>Fall</li>
              <li>Prerequisite: LING 201.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
              </div>
