    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Russian (Arts)              : The Golden Age of Russian literature: from Pushkin, Lermontov, and Gogol to the first works of Dostoevsky and Tolstoy. This course traces the rise of a coherent literary tradition in Russia, exploring authors’ relationships to the burgeoning tradition and to their historical and cultural context.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
